Belgium, 23 September: With regard to testing, a series of decisions have been taken in this area, namely:

To increase the testing capacity of existing triage centres and establishing new screening points. The federated entities are currently working on it;
A call-centre will be set up to group all questions in a single point of information and to reduce the burden on general practitioners;
To set up a platform to book appointments and dispatch requests to the available centres.
To lighten the administrative burden on doctors, a “Corona doctor’s note” will be created in mid-October for certain asymptomatic cases - such as people returning from their holidays, for example;
Or patients can be encouraged to consult their test results online, in particular via the Cozo system or masanté.be.

Regarding travel , it was reminded that since August 1, all persons arriving on Belgian territory after a stay abroad of more than 48 hours must complete the Passenger Locator Form , which can be used to check where the traveler has gone. In addition:
Anyone returning from a red zone should be tested and quarantined, even if he / she shows no symptoms;
If the person returns from an orange zone , it is a recommendation. However, this recommendation should be taken seriously, especially if the person returning from an orange zone has had high-risk contacts;
In addition, citizens are asked to actively participate in contact tracing with the regional call center managers, which makes it possible to contact everyone.

